						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1411 (1540 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Registers gift of two gold chains with pendants set with precious stones. One for the god Periya-Perumāḷ and the other for the goddess by Periya-Tirumalaidēva Mahārāja, son of Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara Salakkayyadēva Mahārāja. The details of the date viz. <hi rend="bold">Śaka 14[61], Vikārin, Mīṉa ba 13, Saturday, Sadayam</hi> correspond to <hi rend="bold">1540 A.D. March 6, Saturday, ·65, f.d.n. ·02.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
